It was so cool to see a more in-depth look into what may be lacking in my life and how to focus more on attaining more fulfillment.

node.text:
‼️ SWIPE 👉 ‼️ How do you help someone you love who struggles with anxiety?
〰️
✅ DONT force confrontation. Actually, the word “confrontation” may sound scary for some people...so maybe just think about how to approach someone in a calm and supportive way. When he/she is READY! ❤️👍
〰️
✅ Educate yourself on anxiety and mental health! It’s very important to learn what you can on what anxiety is and acknowledge the reality of the disorder. It can be debilitating and can manifest biologically, emotionally, socially, etc. 
〰️
✅ VALIDATE! VALIDATE! VALIDATE! This is probably the most important thing you can do to help an anxious person. Make sure to let them know that their feelings ARE VALID! And that they are not “crazy” or “annoying” or “stupid” ...say something like “I can see how much you’re going through and I am so sorry you’re feeling like this. I’m here for you and will help you through this.” 
〰️
✅ Be their advocate for change and encourage therapy! Create a safe space for your anxious loved one. Create an open conversation and an open mind toward therapy and REDUCE THE STIGMA! Therapy is healing!
〰️
✅ Ask your loved one what you can do to help him/her. May seem small, but this can be SO healing for the anxious mind. Knowing you have a support system, who will not judge you, is 👍👍👍
〰️
Do you have any more tips on how a loved one can help when you struggle with anxiety? Comment below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
